"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-07-12-How-a-Chinese-deliveryman-is-running-his-way-to-Paris-2024-Olympics-1vaX2hCueXK-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Copied  \\\"Hey Champ!\\\" is a special CGTN series in which Olympic champions and participants from all disciplines are invited to visit schools and local communities in China, have some fun with sports enthusiasts, and reflect on their experience at the Games.  In this episode, CGTN speaks to 39-year-old deliveryman Luan Yushuai, who has registered to run in the upcoming Paris 2024 Marathon Pour Tous, the first-ever Olympic event open to the general public. Is he ready for Paris? How has he trained for the marathon? How does he balance work and life? Take a look!  Official data shows that 40,048 amateur runners were invited to take part in the Games, over 120 of whom are from China.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"